            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rondsculpturen van menselijke of dierlijke figuren of kleine groepen van figuren, steeds ten voeten uit, staande of zittende, meestal in een open ruimte en op een sokkel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常描繪人物、動物、神話生物或一小群人的圓雕作品，尺寸相對較大，可能與真人或實物大小相仿、更大或略小。至於尺寸較小的人物、動物或神話生物雕像則稱為「小雕像」、「小塑像」或使用其他比較適切的詞語；以雕塑之外的其他手法呈現的人物、動物或神話生物的造型則稱為「形象畫(畫像)」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scultura a tutto tondo, di solito ma non sempre di umani, animali, esseri mitici, o piccoli gruppi di figure. Statue hanno dimensioni relativamente grandi. Per rappresentazioni piccole di umani, animali, o esseri mitici, usa "figurine", "statuettes" o un altro termine appropriato. Per rappresentazioni di umani, animali, o esseri mitici nei media diversi dalla scultura, usa "figures (representations)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
